In this case, lay speaker.

00:00:08.099 --> 00:00:11.959
The pulpit. Speaking.

00:00:11.959 --> 00:00:15.940
But, then I was afforded the opportunity

00:00:15.940 --> 00:00:18.950
[clears throat] to become

00:00:18.950 --> 00:00:23.420
a servant. Thanks to the 2012 conference

00:00:23.420 --> 00:00:28.200
of the United Methodist Church, they
approve the legislation to change the name 

00:00:28.270 --> 00:00:31.730
of Lay Speaking ministries to [clears throat]

00:00:31.730 --> 00:00:35.739
Lay Servant ministries. But what does
that mean?

00:00:35.739 --> 00:00:40.109
It means I get out from behind the
lectern as a speaker and I

00:00:40.109 --> 00:00:44.190
become a servant. So what was a Lay
Speaker?

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:47.280
And why is it now a Lay Servant?

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:50.449
Why am I wearing a bow tie coat and tails?

00:00:50.449 --> 00:00:54.569
Why is the earth round? These questions just

00:00:54.569 --> 00:00:59.400
keep piling up don't they? All right, well, I can help you with the Lay Servant questions

00:00:59.499 --> 00:01:00.210
because

00:01:00.210 --> 00:01:03.870
you know that's what we're talking about
on this episode

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:07.000
of Chuck Knows Church.

